  <titles>
    <title type="short" as="introduced">Business Supply Chain Transparency on Trafficking and Slavery Act of 2014</title>
    <title type="official" as="introduced">To amend the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 to require certain companies to disclose information describing any measures the company has taken to identify and address conditions of forced labor, slavery, human trafficking, and the worst forms of child labor within the company's supply chains.</title>
  </titles>
